HEADWORD: Wanhope
<hw>Wan"hope`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>wan</ets>,
<ets>won</ets>, deficient, wanting + <ets>hopa</ets> hope: cf. D.
<ets>wanhoop</ets>. <ets><?/<?/<?/<?/</ets>. See <er>Wane</er>, and
<er>Hope</er>.]</ety> <def>Want of hope; despair; also, faint or
delusive hope; delusion. <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <xex>Piers
Plowman</xex>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Wanhope</xex> and distress.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
